@startuml
actor Client
participant LoginController
participant User
database Postgres

Client -> LoginController: POST /login with username and password
note left: Client initiates login request

LoginController -> User: fetch(username)
note right: Retrieve user by username
User --> LoginController: User object if found

LoginController -> Postgres: md5(password)
note right: Hash the provided password
Postgres --> LoginController: MD5 hash of password

LoginController -> LoginController: Compare hashed password with stored hash
note right: Verify if passwords match

alt Passwords match
    LoginController -> User: token(secret)
    note right: Generate authentication token
    User --> LoginController: JWT token
    LoginController --> Client: Return LoginResponse with token
    note right: Send authentication token to client
else Passwords don't match
    LoginController --> Client: Throw Unauthorized exception with 'Access Denied' message
    note right: Authentication failure
else User not found
    LoginController --> Client: NullPointerException when trying to access user.hashedPassword
    note right: Server error due to null user
end
@enduml